Don't write documentation files unless explicitly requested by the user.

**Why:** User prefers to request documentation only when needed, not as part of every implementation. Auto-generating docs adds files the user didn't ask for and may not want.

**How to apply:** When implementing features, focus on the code implementation only. Do not create README.md, guides, installation docs, or other documentation files unless the user specifically asks for documentation. If documentation would be helpful, mention it as an option but don't create it automatically.
